Lindy Cheesecake
  --Mom
  
Crust:
1 c sifted flour
1/2 c sugar
1 tsp grated lemon zest
1 egg yolk
1/4 c soft butter or margarine
1/2 tsp vanilla

In a small bowl combine flour, sugar, zest, and vanilla. Make a well in center, add yolk and butter; with finger tips mix until it leaves side of bowl. Form into ball and wrap in wax paper. Refrigerate for 1 hr. Preheat oven to 400F. Lightly grease bottom of 9" springform pan. Remove 1/3 of dough and roll out directly on top of pan. Bake 8-10 min or until golden light. Cool. Divide dough up to cover the sides of springform (2" strips, 1/2" from top) press lightly. Refrigerate until filling.

Filling:
5x8 oz package cream cheese
1/4 c sugar
3 tbsp ap flour
5 eggs
2 egg yolks
1/4 tsp vanilla
1/4 c heavy whipping cream
1 1/2 tsp grated lemon zest
1 1/2 tsp grated orange zest

In a large mixing bowl, cream cream cheese, sugar, flour, zests, and vanilla. Add eggs and yolks one at a time, beating after each addition. Don't overmix. Add cream last. Pour filling into prepared crust. Bake for 10 min at 500F, then reduce temp to 250F and bake for 1 hr. Cool on rack for 45 min and refrigerate overnight.



Notes: this is one of my mom's recipes, no idea where she got it from, but she only made it once.
